    {
      "title": "[负面] [h3] I'm currently doing a challenge to play throu...",
      "summary": "[h3] I'm currently doing a challenge to play through a free game in every single category on steam. I then give an honest review using ChatGPT. [/h3]\n\nGame: 61 / 447\n\n[b] Category: Roguelike Deckbuilder [/b]\n\n\"A Deal Best Left on the Table\"\n\nThis roguelike deckbuilder struggles to find its footing. The combat system has potential, but it’s drowned out by a tidal wave of gacha mechanics. Banners, microtransactions, and a grind-heavy progression sap the fun out of what could have been a satisfying standalone experience.\n\nThe game doesn’t make a great first impression either. It launches in a window too big for most screens, starts in a foreign language, and relies on AI translation that’s as clunky as the rest of the presentation. The heavy use of AI-generated art doesn’t help; while some pieces look decent, the overall aesthetic is incoherent and uninspired.\n\nUltimately, the game feels like it’s at odds with itself—part roguelike, part gacha, and neither done particularly well. Unless you’re deeply into gacha games and don’t mind a rough experience, this one is hard to recommend.",
      "source": "steam_review",
      "platform_region": "global",
      "lang": "english",
      "time": "2024-12-02T19:44:27+00:00",
      "url": "https://steamcommunity.com/profiles/76561198275999090/recommended/3052450",
      "engagement": 1,
